meta.name: Alex Witt Reports
meta.description: The latest breaking news, reporting and live coverage of the day's important stories; hosted by trusted NBC News journalists, these dynamic hours offer discussions with newsmakers, journalists and politicians.

videos.title: Episode 169
videos.overview: On MSNBC Live with Alex Witt, veteran news anchor Alex Witt provides up to the minute coverage of the news of the day. Airing Saturday mornings, afternoons and Sunday afternoons, the show is a must-watch destination for the latest on the weekend's news.

videos.title: Episode 15
videos.overview: The Trump administration and ICE are averaging 667 arrests per day as President Trump's crackdown on immigration continues. This has led ICE facilities to be nearly full, prompting Trump to consider his options for ramping up deportations even more. NBC News Investigative Reporter Laura Strickler recaps the latest on immigration and how a startling number of migrants arrested have no criminal record.
